===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|alt2=刂|鼎|刀|ls=ic|t1=[[ding]], a bronze cauldron for cooking or sacrificial rituals|t2=knife}}; hence, the original version is [[𠟭]]. Perhaps it's a reference to carving something (e.g., characters) with a knife on a bronze. Its original meaning was "rule; law".

鼎 was simplified to the unrelated 貝 in the small seal script. Compare {{och-l|貞|gloss=to divine; righteous; firm}} (< [[鼑]]), which underwent the same stylization.

